Swyft Desktop — Research & Development Log

Overview
This project explores building a hybrid mobile-to-desktop launcher system on Android. The goal is to create a desktop-like environment that runs on mobile devices while still allowing full access to installed applications.

Core concept:
- Mobile device acts as a launcher + control layer
- Future expansion toward PC companion interface
- Desktop-style UI rendered using native Android views

Core Architecture (Current State)

UI Hierarchy:
ScrollView
   └ GridLayout
        ├ Button (App tile)
        ├ Button (App tile)
        ├ Button (App tile)

Key Design Decisions:
- ScrollView handles vertical overflow
- GridLayout creates desktop-style multi-column layout
- Buttons represent apps (temporary placeholder for icon tiles)
- 4-column grid chosen for desktop-like layout on mobile

App Discovery System

Function: Get Installed Apps

val intent = Intent(Intent.ACTION_MAIN, null).apply {
    addCategory(Intent.CATEGORY_LAUNCHER)
}

val apps = packageManager.queryIntentActivities(intent, 0)

return apps.map {
    AppInfo(
        name = it.loadLabel(packageManager).toString(),
        packageName = it.activityInfo.packageName
    )
}

Explanation:
- Uses Android PackageManager to retrieve launchable apps
- Filters apps that appear in launcher
- Converts system ResolveInfo objects into AppInfo model

Key Learning:
Android 11+ requires <queries> in AndroidManifest.xml to access full app list.

App Rendering System

private fun renderApps(layout: GridLayout, apps: List<AppInfo>) {
    apps.forEach { app ->
        layout.addView(createAppButton(app))
    }
}

Purpose:
- Dynamically generates UI elements from installed apps
- Connects data layer to UI layer

App Tile Creation System

private fun createAppButton(app: AppInfo): Button {
    return Button(this).apply {
        text = app.name

        setOnClickListener {
            launchApp(app.packageName)
        }

        val params = GridLayout.LayoutParams().apply {
            width = 0
            height = GridLayout.LayoutParams.WRAP_CONTENT
            columnSpec = GridLayout.spec(GridLayout.UNDEFINED, 1f)
        }

        layoutParams = params
    }
}

Key Concepts:
- Each app becomes a Button
- Buttons are generated dynamically at runtime
- GridLayout.LayoutParams controls grid behaviour
- width = 0 enables equal column distribution
- weight system ensures 4-column layout

